    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"id\":\"m001\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# Loan Approval Trend Analysis\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Project Overview\\n\",\"This notebook analyzes loan application and decision data to study approval rates, applicant characteristics, and fairness or imbalance patterns.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\"- Analyze loan approval rates across applicant demographics and loan characteristics.\\n\",\"- Identify factors most associated with approval/rejection.\\n\",\"- Explore potential fairness concerns in lending decisions.\\n\",\"- Practice responsible data analysis for sensitive domains.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Business / Research Problem\\n\",\"Lending institutions must balance risk management with fair access to credit. This analysis explores patterns in approval decisions.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Why This Analysis Matters\\n\",\"Disparate approval rates across demographic groups can indicate bias, whether intentional or algorithmic, and may have regulatory consequences.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"id\":\"m002\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Dataset Overview\\n\",\"Synthetic dataset of **5,000 loan applications** with applicant attributes and approval outcomes.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\",\"Synthetically generated for educational purposes.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"id\":\"c001\",\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\nfor pkg in [\\\"pandas\\\", \\\"numpy\\\", \\\"matplotlib\\\", \\\"seaborn\\\", \\\"scipy\\\"]:\\n    try:\\n        importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n    except ImportError:\\n        subprocess.check_call([sys.executable, \\\"-m\\\", \\\"pip\\\", \\\"install\\\", \\\"-q\\\", pkg])\\nprint(\\\"Environment ready.\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"id\":\"c002\",\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import numpy as np\\nimport pandas as pd\\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\nimport seaborn as sns\\nfrom scipy import stats\\nimport warnings\\nwarnings.filterwarnings(\\\"ignore\\\")\\nsns.set_style(\\\"whitegrid\\\")\\n%matplotlib inline\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"id\":\"c003\",\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"SEED = 42\\nN = 5000\\nrng = np.random.default_rng(SEED)\\n\\nrows = []\\nfor i in range(N):\\n    income = max(20000, int(rng.normal(60000, 25000)))\\n    loan_amount = max(1000, int(rng.normal(20000, 12000)))\\n    credit_score = int(np.clip(rng.normal(690, 55), 300, 850))\\n    employment = rng.choice([\\\"Employed\\\", \\\"Self-Employed\\\", \\\"Unemployed\\\"], p=[0.65, 0.25, 0.10])\\n    loan_purpose = rng.choice([\\\"Home\\\", \\\"Auto\\\", \\\"Personal\\\", \\\"Education\\\", \\\"Business\\\"])\\n    dti = np.clip(rng.normal(0.32, 0.12), 0.05, 0.75)\\n    \\n    # Approval based on factors\\n    score = credit_score / 850 * 0.4 + (1 - dti) * 0.25 + (income / 150000) * 0.2\\n    score += 0.1 if employment == \\\"Employed\\\" else -0.05 if employment == \\\"Unemployed\\\" else 0\\n    score += rng.normal(0, 0.05)\\n    approved = int(score > 0.45)\\n    \\n    rows.append({\\\"app_id\\\": f\\\"APP{i+1:05d}\\\", \\\"income\\\": income, \\\"loan_amount\\\": loan_amount,\\n                 \\\"credit_score\\\": credit_score, \\\"employment\\\": employment,\\n                 \\\"loan_purpose\\\": loan_purpose, \\\"dti_ratio\\\": round(dti, 3), \\\"approved\\\": approved})\\n\\ndf = pd.DataFrame(rows)\\nprint(f\\\"Dataset: {df.shape}, Approval rate: {df['approved'].mean():.1%}\\\")\\ndf.head()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"id\":\"c004\",\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"print(f\\\"Missing: {df.isnull().sum().sum()}, ✅ Validation passed.\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"id\":\"c005\",\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(14, 10))\\n\\ndf.groupby(\\\"employment\\\")[\\\"approved\\\"].mean().plot(kind=\\\"bar\\\", ax=axes[0,0], color=\\\"steelblue\\\")\\naxes[0,0].set_title(\\\"Approval Rate by Employment\\\")\\naxes[0,0].tick_params(axis=\\\"x\\\", rotation=0)\\n\\ndf.groupby(\\\"loan_purpose\\\")[\\\"approved\\\"].mean().sort_values().plot(kind=\\\"barh\\\", ax=axes[0,1], color=\\\"coral\\\")\\naxes[0,1].set_title(\\\"Approval Rate by Purpose\\\")\\n\\nfor label, color in [(0, \\\"#e74c3c\\\"), (1, \\\"#2ecc71\\\")]:\\n    subset = df[df[\\\"approved\\\"]==label]\\n    axes[1,0].hist(subset[\\\"credit_score\\\"], bins=30, alpha=0.5, color=color, label=\\\"Approved\\\" if label else \\\"Rejected\\\")\\naxes[1,0].set_title(\\\"Credit Score Distribution\\\")\\naxes[1,0].legend()\\n\\nsns.boxplot(data=df, x=\\\"approved\\\", y=\\\"dti_ratio\\\", ax=axes[1,1], palette=[\\\"#e74c3c\\\",\\\"#2ecc71\\\"])\\naxes[1,1].set_title(\\\"DTI Ratio by Approval Status\\\")\\naxes[1,1].set_xticklabels([\\\"Rejected\\\", \\\"Approved\\\"])\\n\\nplt.tight_layout()\\nplt.show()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"id\":\"c006\",\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"# Correlation heatmap\\nnumeric = [\\\"credit_score\\\", \\\"income\\\", \\\"loan_amount\\\", \\\"dti_ratio\\\", \\\"approved\\\"]\\nfig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))\\nsns.heatmap(df[numeric].corr(), annot=True, fmt=\\\".2f\\\", cmap=\\\"coolwarm\\\", center=0, ax=ax)\\nax.set_title(\\\"Correlation Matrix\\\")\\nplt.tight_layout()\\nplt.show()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"id\":\"m003\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Key Findings\\n\",\"1. **Credit score is the dominant approval factor.**\\n\",\"2. **Employed applicants are approved at significantly higher rates** than unemployed.\\n\",\"3. **DTI ratio inversely correlates with approval** — high debt loads reduce chances.\\n\",\"4. **Income provides a moderate positive effect** on approval probability.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Limitations\\n\",\"- Synthetic data; real lending decisions involve more complex underwriting.\\n\",\"- No temporal trends analyzed.\\n\",\"- Fairness analysis limited without protected attribute data.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Recommendations / Next Steps\\n\",\"1. Set transparent approval criteria based on credit score + DTI.\\n\",\"2. Monitor approval rates by demographic group for fairness.\\n\",\"3. Build a predictive model and test for disparate impact.\\n\",\"4. Implement appeals process for borderline rejections.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Common Mistakes\\n\",\"1. Relying on a single factor for approval decisions.\\n\",\"2. Not testing for bias in historical approval patterns.\\n\",\"3. Ignoring the cost of both false approvals (defaults) and false rejections (lost business).\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Mini Challenge\\n\",\"1. Build a logistic regression model for approval prediction.\\n\",\"2. Create a scorecard assigning points for each factor.\\n\",\"3. Test whether approval rates differ for equal credit scores across employment types.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\",\"- **Credit score and DTI ratio drive most approval decisions.**\\n\",\"- **Employment status adds significant predictive value.**\\n\",\"- **Fairness monitoring should be built into any lending analysis.**\"]}\n",
    " ],\n",
